The paper deals with computing the Fr\'{e}chet distance between two polygonal curves, which is a fundamental problem in computational geometry. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also presents a pseudo-polynomial time algorithm, which involves dynamic programming, and hence, it could be categorized under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also discusses the construction of weighted shortest paths, which could be categorized under cs.GR (Graphics) or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the paper presents a novel approach to computing the Fr\'{e}chet distance, which could be categorized under cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics).
